Rating: 3
I've been making versions of this great recipe for almost ten years. For alternatives, try soaking or poaching the apricots in sherry or orange liquer, and/or a touch of vanilla. Friends and family seem to like double the topping.

Rating: 4
I really enjoy making this recipe and have done so on numerous occasions!! I have discovered that when working on a limited time frame, one can boil the sweet potatoes until soft and microwave the apricots until rehydrated. It's virtually the same as the oven roasting method but half the time. I also added orange juice instead of the sugar.

Rating: 3
This recipe was a huge success at Christmas dinner. A non sweet potato-eating guest went so far to grab a second-helping after dinner. I added a teaspoon and a half of pumpkin pie spice for a little extra zip.